# T28 IO Ring Orchestrator — toolchain configuration
# Bridge connection is managed by virtuoso-bridge-lite.
# Configure it once with: virtuoso-bridge init && virtuoso-bridge start
# See README.md > Prerequisites.

# Path to your T28 cds.lib (used by Calibre strmout/si wrappers)
# This should be the REMOTE Linux path visible from the compute server.
CDS_LIB_PATH_28=/home/chenzc_intern25/TSMC28/llm_IO/cds.lib

# === Filesystem Mode (VB_FS_MODE) ===
# Controls how files are exchanged between your machine and the compute server.
#
# Mode 1 — "shared": Group servers share filesystem via NFS.
#   Your workstation and the compute server see the same paths.
#   AMS_OUTPUT_ROOT should be a path accessible from the compute server.
#   CDS_LIB_PATH_28 should be on the shared filesystem.
#
# Mode 2 — "remote": Your Windows PC, compute server in another group.
#   Scripts are pushed via SSH to /tmp/vb_t28_calibre/ on the remote.
#   After Calibre runs, results are pulled back via SSH.
#   CDS_LIB_PATH_28 should be the REMOTE Linux path to cds.lib.
#
# If VB_FS_MODE is not set, the system auto-detects based on whether
# AMS_OUTPUT_ROOT is reachable from the remote server.
#
#VB_FS_MODE=shared
#VB_FS_MODE=remote

# Optional output path controls:
# 1) If AMS_OUTPUT_ROOT is set, scripts write reports/artifacts under this path.
# 2) Else if AMS_IO_AGENT_PATH is set, scripts use ${AMS_IO_AGENT_PATH}/output.
# 3) Else scripts use ./output under current working directory.
#AMS_OUTPUT_ROOT=/absolute/path/to/workspace/output
#AMS_IO_AGENT_PATH=/absolute/path/to/workspace
